{5 EGS 28/24 Spectrum-kortin tekninen erittely
{5 -------------------------------------------

Bus interface           Zorro II/Zorro III auto-sensing. Zorro II interface
provides a 16-bit       to Amiga FAST RAM and storage devices. Zorro III
                        uses a full 32-bit interface.

Internal Graphics Architecture: 32-bit Video Local Bus (VLB) emulation.

                        Data are long-word aligned and pixel-packed for
                        maximum RAM conservation (RGBR/GBRG/BRGB/...)

Frame Buffer            1 or 2 MB if Display RAM (DRAM), with 16- or 32-bit
                        access to Amiga FAST RAM via Zorro II or Zorro III
                        bus.

DRAM                    CAS Control, 70 ns 512k chips in SOJ package

Maximum pixel display speed: 28,000,000 pixels/second
                                @ 24 bits/pixel (16.7 M colors)
                             80,000,000 pixels/second
                                @  8 bits/pixel (256 colors)

Maximum Display Resolution: Programmable from 320 x 200 to
                                1600 x 1280 (interlaced) @ 4-bits
                                1280 x 1024 (interlaced) @ 8-bits
                                1024 x 768 (interlaced) @ 16-bits
                                800 x 600 (non-interlaced) @ 24-bits


